WEBVTT

00:58.309 --> 00:59.477
SHAGGY:
That's my pal.

01:00.186 --> 01:01.729
Scooby-Dooby-Doo!

01:19.121 --> 01:22.416
SHAGGY: Whoa, like, these Turkish
mountain roads are really rocky.

01:28.506 --> 01:30.800
I'll say.

01:31.008 --> 01:34.637
Just hang on, gang. We should be
at Professor Brigston's camp any minute.

01:34.804 --> 01:37.431
Imagine him discovering
a whole city...

01:37.598 --> 01:40.268
...that's been buried
for thousands of years.

01:40.434 --> 01:42.937
And we'll be among the first to see it.

01:43.104 --> 01:45.398
Like, how about a little Turkish music,
Scoob?

01:45.564 --> 01:47.400
[PANTING]

01:59.870 --> 02:01.706
[GIGGLING]

02:11.757 --> 02:13.843
[GROWLING]

02:25.521 --> 02:27.523
FRED:
Well, this looks like the place.

02:27.690 --> 02:30.443
This area is restricted. No visitors.

02:30.609 --> 02:33.738
But we've come at the direct invitation
of Dr. Brigston, sir.

02:33.904 --> 02:35.406
Dr. Brigston? Hmm.

02:35.573 --> 02:37.950
Very well. His tent is over there.

02:46.250 --> 02:50.004
DAPHNE: Jeepers, professor.
This is really exciting.

02:50.171 --> 02:53.466
We're anxious to see what
you've discovered in the ancient city.

02:53.632 --> 02:57.428
I'm afraid, my friends,
there won't be much to see.

02:57.595 --> 02:58.971
We've had to stop digging.

02:59.138 --> 03:00.890
DAPHNE:
Stop? How come?

03:01.057 --> 03:05.728
BRIGSTON: Because all my workers
were frightened away by the Tar Monster.

03:05.895 --> 03:07.438
Huh?

03:07.646 --> 03:10.232
Like, what do you mean Tar Monster?

03:10.399 --> 03:13.778
This area has been known
for centuries for its tar pools.

03:13.944 --> 03:17.073
The people have always believed
the ancient city of Byzantius...

03:17.239 --> 03:19.950
...was under the protection
of a legendary creature...

03:20.117 --> 03:24.288
...that lived in the pools.
The Tar Monster.

03:27.291 --> 03:28.709
Having trouble, Scoob?

03:28.876 --> 03:30.961
[GIGGLING]

03:49.563 --> 03:51.023
[SIGHS]

03:51.232 --> 03:52.858
The trouble began yesterday...

03:53.025 --> 03:57.863
...when we finally reached
the inner sanctum of the ancient city.

03:59.490 --> 04:01.575
We were about to open
this sanctum...

04:01.742 --> 04:06.205
...when we found an ancient curse
carved in the stone.

04:06.372 --> 04:10.292
It said, "This city is under protection
of the Tar Creature.

04:10.459 --> 04:13.045
Intruders, beware."

04:13.212 --> 04:15.381
Suddenly, there was a terrible roar.

04:15.548 --> 04:17.966
[MONSTER ROARING]

04:18.134 --> 04:19.760
And then he appeared.

04:19.927 --> 04:23.055
The Tar Monster. A terrifying sight.

04:23.222 --> 04:26.600
Tar dripping from its body
as it came toward us.

04:26.767 --> 04:29.437
The workmen ran away.

04:31.981 --> 04:33.899
And that's not the worst of it.

04:34.066 --> 04:37.069
Like, | was afraid
you were gonna say that.

04:37.236 --> 04:40.072
Come with me. I'll show you.

04:42.074 --> 04:43.784
Zoinks. Like, what happened?

04:43.951 --> 04:48.414
Last night, | heard my assistant,
Mr. Stoner, shouting for help.

04:48.581 --> 04:50.749
| ran over here to help and found this.

04:50.916 --> 04:52.793
His tent destroyed.

04:52.960 --> 04:54.837
Zoinks. What happened to him?

04:55.004 --> 04:57.631
We don't know.
He's gone. Disappeared.

04:57.798 --> 04:59.175
[BOTH GULPING]

04:59.341 --> 05:01.719
Like, the Tar Monster got him?

05:01.886 --> 05:05.347
Here's a picture of Stoner,
streaked with tar.

05:05.514 --> 05:07.933
And look at this,
there's tar everywhere.

05:08.100 --> 05:12.104
Come, we must return to my tent
before the creature comes back.

05:12.271 --> 05:13.564
-Comes back?
-Comes back?

05:15.399 --> 05:17.359
VELMA:
Jinkies, that sure is awful...

05:17.526 --> 05:20.821
...about your assistant disappearing
like that, Professor Brigston.

05:20.988 --> 05:22.364
What'll you do now?

05:22.531 --> 05:26.869
We are certain that a priceless treasure
awaits us in the inner sanctum.

05:27.036 --> 05:30.080
| must carry on,
by myself if necessary.

05:31.957 --> 05:34.043
[WHIMPERING]

05:37.004 --> 05:39.924
Zoinks. Like, it's him.

05:47.681 --> 05:48.974
[CRASHING]

05:49.141 --> 05:53.270
Scooby-Doo, where are you?

05:53.521 --> 05:55.022
[WHIMPERING]

05:56.524 --> 05:58.234
BRIGSTON:
There's no need to worry.

05:58.400 --> 06:01.070
It's only my foreman, Ben Gazi.

06:01.237 --> 06:03.405
He will take you to your tents
for the night.

06:03.572 --> 06:07.451
Thank you, professor. Come on,
everybody, let's get some sleep.

06:08.702 --> 06:09.995
SHAGGY:
What a trip, eh, Scoob?

06:10.162 --> 06:13.082
Tar Monsters, disappearing people.
Ha-ha-ha.

06:13.249 --> 06:16.085
It's enough to drive a person batty.
Scoob? Scoob?

06:16.252 --> 06:17.378
[SNORING]

06:18.963 --> 06:20.714
[GARGLING LOUDLY]

06:28.264 --> 06:29.723
[YAWNS]

06:32.977 --> 06:34.520
[SIGHS]

06:34.687 --> 06:36.772
[SHAGGY GARGLING]

06:41.694 --> 06:43.153
[SWALLOWS]

06:45.447 --> 06:47.533
[SNORING]

06:59.169 --> 07:03.173
Come on, Scoob,
knock off all that snoring.

07:04.174 --> 07:06.385
[MONSTER GROWLING]

07:06.594 --> 07:09.597
Wake up, Scoob,
or I'll never get to sleep.

07:09.763 --> 07:11.849
[ROARING]

07:13.434 --> 07:17.187
Oh, boy.
Like, it's only the Tar Monster.

07:18.355 --> 07:19.690
Zoinks!

07:19.857 --> 07:21.942
[GROWLING]

07:22.901 --> 07:25.696
Scoob. Scoob. Let's get out of here!

07:27.156 --> 07:29.408
You say something, Shaggy?

07:29.575 --> 07:31.577
[MONSTER ROARING]

07:32.119 --> 07:33.329
[WHIMPERING]

07:33.495 --> 07:34.622
Shaggy?

07:34.788 --> 07:36.874
[ROARING]

07:42.338 --> 07:43.881
SHAGGY:
Help!

07:44.048 --> 07:46.258
SCOOBY: The Tar Monster!
SHAGGY: We saw him!

07:46.425 --> 07:48.427
SCOOBY:
The Tar Monster!

07:48.594 --> 07:50.971
VELMA:
Wait a second. Slow down.

07:51.138 --> 07:54.475
-You actually saw the Tar Monster?
-Yeah.

07:54.642 --> 07:59.563
He was this tall and this wide.

07:59.730 --> 08:00.981
FRED:
Where did you see him?

08:01.148 --> 08:02.775
SHAGGY:
He came after us in our tent.

08:02.941 --> 08:06.070
-Jeepers.
-We better have a look.

08:07.655 --> 08:09.657
DAPHNE:
There's tar everywhere.

08:09.823 --> 08:12.910
For once,
you two weren't imagining things.

08:13.077 --> 08:16.080
Let's follow his tracks
and see what we can find. Come on.

08:16.246 --> 08:18.332
-Uh-uh!
VELMA: Oh, Scooby...

08:18.499 --> 08:22.753
...sometimes | think you have a real
yellow streak right down your back.

08:22.920 --> 08:23.962
Yep.

08:24.129 --> 08:26.465
[GIGGLES]

08:26.799 --> 08:28.467
FRED:
Quit the clowning, Scoob.

08:28.634 --> 08:31.178
There's no time to waste.

08:33.389 --> 08:38.686
Jinkies, the tracks end at this tar pool
as if he went down into it.

08:38.852 --> 08:40.395
But that's impossible.

08:40.562 --> 08:43.065
Not for a Tar Monster.

08:43.232 --> 08:44.608
Hey, look at this.

08:44.775 --> 08:47.903
DAPHNE: What is it?
-Looks like an ancient piece of pottery.

08:48.070 --> 08:49.571
But what's it doing here?

08:49.738 --> 08:52.991
FRED: | don't know,
but | bet the professor will.

08:53.158 --> 08:54.243
Let's go.

09:00.582 --> 09:02.835
KARIM: Our government agrees
with your decision...

09:03.001 --> 09:05.921
...to recover our ancient treasures
without delay, professor.

09:06.088 --> 09:09.133
| will go with you and your friends
to open the inner sanctum.

09:09.299 --> 09:11.260
After what happened last night...

09:11.427 --> 09:15.013
...we're more interested than ever
in the mystery of the Tar Monster.

09:15.180 --> 09:17.766
Good. You can witness
what will surely be...

09:17.933 --> 09:20.394
...one of the most valuable finds
of the century.

09:20.561 --> 09:23.272
Hey, you two, how's breakfast
coming along?

09:23.439 --> 09:25.983
Terrific. You might say
I'm really cooking.

09:26.150 --> 09:29.153
Ha-ha-ha. Really cooking, Scoob.
Ha-ha-ha.

09:35.367 --> 09:36.577
[GIGGLING]

09:38.495 --> 09:40.414
BRIGSTON:
We'll get started right after breakfast.

09:40.581 --> 09:44.042
Like, keep the toast a-popping, Scoob.

09:45.544 --> 09:50.299
Okay. More toast coming up.

09:58.265 --> 09:59.850
[GIGGLING]

10:00.058 --> 10:04.521
| will get my equipment and meet you all
at the excavation in 15 minutes.

10:04.688 --> 10:06.523
We'll be there.

10:06.982 --> 10:11.153
DAPHNE: Jeepers, there's a whole city
down here...

10:11.945 --> 10:15.532
...with enough statues
and art objects to fill a museum.

10:15.699 --> 10:18.744
The richest treasures lie,
as yet untouched...

10:18.911 --> 10:20.746
...in the inner sanctum of the city.

10:23.791 --> 10:25.417
Gah!

10:28.045 --> 10:29.213
[STATUE SHATTERING]

10:40.098 --> 10:42.851
Funny. Like, that statue looks familiar.

10:43.018 --> 10:44.645
Yeah.

10:44.812 --> 10:47.981
Professor, what happened
to the mighty city of Byzantius?

10:48.148 --> 10:51.026
Yeah, how come it's buried
so far beneath the surface?

10:51.193 --> 10:54.446
Our research indicates
there was a giant earthquake...

10:54.613 --> 10:57.783
...that dropped
this entire region hundreds of feet.

10:57.950 --> 10:59.660
-Jeepers.
-And then...

10:59.827 --> 11:01.620
...the surrounding hills collapsed...

11:01.787 --> 11:04.039
...burying the city forever.

11:04.206 --> 11:06.375
No wonder everything
looks almost untouched...

11:06.542 --> 11:09.586
...as if people were still living here.

11:11.380 --> 11:15.259
And here we are. Very spot
where the workmen ran away.

11:15.425 --> 11:18.303
And, like, there's the curse
of the Tar Monster.

11:18.470 --> 11:19.721
[GASPS]

11:21.348 --> 11:25.602
This is a great moment in history.

11:26.311 --> 11:28.689
Professor,
the treasures have been stolen.

11:29.648 --> 11:32.985
Look. The Tar Monster.

11:38.198 --> 11:39.241
[GASPS]

11:39.408 --> 11:40.617
[WHIMPERING]

11:42.786 --> 11:45.831
Zoinks! Like, run for your lives.

11:45.998 --> 11:48.667
VELMA:
Relax. It's only a statue.

11:48.834 --> 11:50.419
Statue?

11:50.586 --> 11:51.712
[GIGGLING]

11:51.920 --> 11:56.508
It's been here for centuries
to guard the inner sanctum treasures.

11:56.675 --> 12:00.262
Some guard.
Like, there's nothing left to steal. Ha-ha.

12:00.429 --> 12:03.265
-Yeah.
-Professor, Karim, look.

12:03.432 --> 12:06.226
DAPHNE: Jeepers, the tracks
of the Tar Monster.

12:06.393 --> 12:07.519
KARIM:
But that's impossible.

12:07.686 --> 12:10.022
No one could get past my guards
at the entrance.

12:10.188 --> 12:14.359
Which means he must have found
another way to get down here.

12:14.526 --> 12:17.029
- Must sound the alarm.
-I'll come up with you.

12:17.195 --> 12:18.614
Like, that's a swell idea.

12:18.780 --> 12:21.658
Let's get out of this creepy place.

12:21.867 --> 12:25.120
Hold it, you two. We've got to track
down the Tar Monster.

12:25.287 --> 12:28.790
Oh, boy. Wouldn't you know
he'd say that?

12:29.166 --> 12:32.836
Looks like our Tar Monster
has been here several times.

12:33.003 --> 12:35.547
There are tracks down both corridors.

12:35.714 --> 12:38.926
Which means we'll have to split up
to look for clues.

12:39.092 --> 12:41.136
-Split up?
-Uh-uh.

12:41.303 --> 12:44.890
Oh, Scooby.
What could possibly happen to you?

12:49.394 --> 12:50.854
[GIGGLING]

12:51.063 --> 12:54.524
Shaggy, you and Scooby go that way
and see what you can find.

12:54.691 --> 12:57.027
We'll head down this way.

12:57.194 --> 12:58.528
Like, careful, Scoob.

12:58.695 --> 13:00.697
There's a lot of tar along here.

13:00.864 --> 13:02.574
Yeah.

13:06.244 --> 13:07.788
Yuch.

13:12.751 --> 13:14.419
[SIGHS]

13:18.966 --> 13:21.051
[WHIMPERING]

13:24.930 --> 13:25.973
[THUDS]

13:30.102 --> 13:32.437
Shaggy, wait for me.

13:32.604 --> 13:34.690
Scooby? Scooby-Doo?

13:35.232 --> 13:37.567
Where are you?

13:37.734 --> 13:40.028
Shaggy.

13:43.907 --> 13:45.492
Uh-oh.

13:47.577 --> 13:49.329
Whoa!

13:51.498 --> 13:54.918
Scooby, like, help!

13:55.210 --> 13:56.712
Oh. Oh, boy.

13:56.878 --> 13:58.130
I'm coming, Shag.

13:58.296 --> 13:59.673
[CRASHING]

14:03.719 --> 14:05.804
[GIGGLING]

14:09.224 --> 14:13.562
Look, Scoob, like, this is the same kind
of lid we found back at the tar pool.

14:13.729 --> 14:17.357
Yeah, maybe it's a clue.

14:18.066 --> 14:22.654
DAPHNE: Jeepers, this underground city
is @ maze of corridors and tunnels.

14:22.821 --> 14:25.741
VELMA: It's a good thing we have
the tar tracks to follow.

14:25.907 --> 14:28.410
We could be lost down here forever.

14:28.577 --> 14:32.581
Look, | had a hunch we'd find this.
Another tar pool.

14:32.748 --> 14:37.085
And the tracks end here, just as they did
at the pool above ground.

14:37.502 --> 14:41.256
Hmm. It looks like we're finally
onto something.

14:41.423 --> 14:46.261
Right. Let's find Shaggy and Scooby
to see if they came up with anything.

14:48.346 --> 14:50.640
Like, the trouble
with following these tracks...

14:50.807 --> 14:53.435
...ils we might run into the monster
that's making them.

14:53.602 --> 14:56.897
-Yeah.
-Oh, boy, if | live to be a hundred...

14:57.064 --> 14:59.983
...I'Il never forget
that Tar Monster roar.

15:00.150 --> 15:01.860
[MONSTER ROARING]

15:02.027 --> 15:04.780
Ha-ha. Pretty good, Scoob.
You sound just like him.

15:04.946 --> 15:06.364
[MONSTER ROARING]

15:06.531 --> 15:10.118
Ha-ha. | mean, that's terrific, Scoob. I--

15:10.827 --> 15:11.870
[WHIMPERING]

15:12.037 --> 15:13.080
Zoinks!

15:13.288 --> 15:15.373
[ROARING]

15:18.001 --> 15:20.378
In here, Scoob.

15:20.545 --> 15:23.131
Oh-ho-ho.
This calls for a fast makeup job.

15:30.639 --> 15:32.182
[ROARS]

15:32.390 --> 15:35.477
[BEGINNING TO SNEEZE]

15:35.644 --> 15:37.270
[SNEEZES]

15:41.274 --> 15:44.111
[MONSTER YELLS THEN ROARS]

15:47.489 --> 15:49.449
[ROARING]

16:07.801 --> 16:08.844
[CRASHING]

16:10.095 --> 16:11.138
[MONSTER ROARING]

16:11.304 --> 16:13.390
[BOTH SCREAMING]

16:17.853 --> 16:19.938
[BUZZING]

16:23.817 --> 16:25.902
[SIGHING]

16:28.697 --> 16:30.782
[MONSTER ROARING]

16:32.701 --> 16:34.786
[CRYING]

16:37.122 --> 16:39.332
Looks like no sign of Scoob or Shag.

16:39.499 --> 16:40.584
What's that?

16:40.750 --> 16:42.669
It's a workman's toolkit.

16:42.836 --> 16:45.672
What's it doing way back here?

16:45.839 --> 16:47.257
Look at this.

16:48.675 --> 16:52.721
FRED: It's a map of the underground city
streaked with tar.

16:53.054 --> 16:54.598
And there's the inner sanctum.

16:54.764 --> 16:57.350
This map is just the clue we needed.

16:57.517 --> 17:00.562
Right. Now this mystery
is starting to make sense.

17:00.729 --> 17:02.439
Come on.

17:04.107 --> 17:07.109
Faster, Scoob.
Like, he's gaining on us.

17:07.277 --> 17:08.486
[ROARING]

17:14.367 --> 17:17.037
Welcome, welcome, welcome
to our photo studio, sir.

17:17.204 --> 17:19.664
We've got a special today,
for monsters only.

17:19.830 --> 17:22.209
Three prints for a dollar.

17:22.375 --> 17:24.586
Say cheese.

17:37.098 --> 17:39.184
[ROARING]

17:46.900 --> 17:49.819
Very good.
We'll mail you your print, sir.

17:54.908 --> 17:57.327
[GROWLING]

17:58.078 --> 18:00.080
Hey, like, | got rid of him.

18:00.247 --> 18:02.332
[ROARING]

18:02.540 --> 18:04.000
Zoinks!

18:04.167 --> 18:05.961
[GIGGLING]

18:06.127 --> 18:08.630
Shaggy. Wait.

18:16.805 --> 18:19.432
Scooby-Doo? Scooby-Doo?

18:22.686 --> 18:26.189
Zoinks! The Tar Monster.

18:27.274 --> 18:28.316
[CRASHING]

18:28.483 --> 18:29.526
VELMA:
It's Shaggy.

18:29.693 --> 18:31.861
-Are you okay, Shag?
-Yeah.

18:32.028 --> 18:33.113
[SOBS]

18:33.280 --> 18:34.864
But the monster's got Scoob.

18:35.031 --> 18:36.992
[SOBBING THEN BLOWS NOSE]

18:37.158 --> 18:39.035
Oh, woe is me, woe is me.

18:39.202 --> 18:40.870
I'll never forget you, old buddy.

18:41.037 --> 18:42.163
[SOBBING]

18:42.330 --> 18:44.958
Oh, my old buddy. My old pal.

18:45.125 --> 18:47.210
Oh, hi, Scoob.

18:47.711 --> 18:49.421
Oh, he was like a brother to me.

18:49.587 --> 18:52.299
I'll miss him so mu--

18:53.300 --> 18:56.261
-Scooby.
-Yeah.

18:58.513 --> 19:00.598
Thanks a lot, Scoob.

19:00.765 --> 19:02.225
Take a look at this vent.

19:02.392 --> 19:04.352
| think we found another clue.

19:04.519 --> 19:07.272
-It's an air compressor.
-Huh?

19:07.439 --> 19:11.818
Like, what's an air compressor doing
in a city that's thousands of years old?

19:11.985 --> 19:15.613
-Now we know what's been happening.
-We do?

19:15.780 --> 19:17.782
FRED: Give me a hand
with this compressor, Shag.

19:17.949 --> 19:20.994
We're gonna use it
to capture the Tar Monster.

19:22.037 --> 19:23.079
Like, what's going on?

19:23.246 --> 19:26.082
FRED: This is set up so the compressor
won't start pumping air...

19:26.249 --> 19:29.085
...until we get back up to the surface.

19:38.219 --> 19:41.264
DAPHNE:
Gee, | sure hope this works.

19:41.431 --> 19:44.559
-Look, it is working.
FRED: Right.

19:44.726 --> 19:48.146
That ought to force our monster friend
to the surface.

19:50.398 --> 19:52.484
[MONSTER ROARING]

19:57.572 --> 19:58.823
VELMA:
There he is.

19:58.990 --> 20:00.825
SHAGGY:
Zoinks! Like, he's getting away.

20:02.869 --> 20:04.913
DAPHNE:
Jeepers, we got him.

20:05.080 --> 20:08.249
Wait till the professor sees this.

20:09.167 --> 20:13.046
Now let's see
who the Tar Monster really is.

20:13.797 --> 20:17.509
BRIGSTON: Why, it's Stoner,
my missing assistant.

20:17.675 --> 20:18.843
That's right, professor.

20:19.010 --> 20:23.431
He posed as the Tar Monster
to frighten off the local workers.

20:23.598 --> 20:26.684
That way, he could sneak
into the inner sanctum...

20:26.851 --> 20:30.605
...and steal its treasures
before you could find them.

20:30.772 --> 20:32.941
But how did he get past my guards?

20:33.108 --> 20:36.111
The answer to that begins
with that ancient piece of pottery...

20:36.277 --> 20:39.114
...we found at the tar pool
after following his tracks.

20:39.280 --> 20:41.950
The pottery had to come
from the ancient city below.

20:42.117 --> 20:44.953
So when we found
the connecting pool down there...

20:45.120 --> 20:47.789
...we realized how he was getting
into the city.

20:47.956 --> 20:49.082
| get it.

20:49.249 --> 20:50.792
Like, he used his scuba gear...

20:50.959 --> 20:53.795
-...to dive down through the tar.
-Yeah.

20:53.962 --> 20:56.798
FRED: All that's left now
is to find the treasure.

20:56.965 --> 21:00.176
Stoner, where have you
